 Find out what controller you're using. The buttons you press to drift depend on this. Play with your controller for a while to get used to it. Start off using Automatic drift to help acquire you to your controller further. Learn about your vehicle. Are you going to be using a kart? Are you going to be using a bike? In addition to using either a kart or bike, you have inner-drift bikes and outer-drift bikes. Inner-drift bikes are those bikes who drift inward upon drifting. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/9\/99\/Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/9\/99\/Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/aid3066990-v4-728px-Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Outer-drift bikes are those bikes who drift outward upon drifting (as shown in the video below). {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/06\/Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-3Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/0\/06\/Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-3Bullet2.jpg\/aid3066990-v4-728px-Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"} Once you have gotten familiar with your vehicle, you're ready to select manual. Drifting on each controller is different with different buttons to press. On the Wii wheel and Wii remote and nunchuk, you're going to want to hold down the B button (located on the back of the Wii remote) to drift. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e2\/Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/e\/e2\/Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/aid3066990-v4-728px-Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

On the classic controller, classic controller pro, and GameCube controller, you're going to want to hold down either the B or R button. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/14\/Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/1\/14\/Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/aid3066990-v4-728px-Drift-on-Mario-Kart-Wii-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":269,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"426","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"} Continue to practice. You're not going to master it off of one try. Continue to practice until you feel you have a good grasp on it. Drift using other characters or vehicles. Once you have a good grasp on drifting, select other characters or vehicles and see if you can drift just as well as you did before.
